messages.text: So does the next question involve anything burning down?
Have you been talking to my friends or something?
I kinda have a thing about singing.
So I was around lots of blues music growing up.
And I sing in a band at weekends.
We‚Äôre not great, but we‚Äôre not terrible either.
No, I mean, I HATE singing.
Yeah. I haven‚Äôt sung since Junior High.
How about singing along to the radio when no one‚Äôs in the car?
Any nieces or nephews you sing to?
I don‚Äôt have nieces and nephews.
My younger sister is only sixteen.
That‚Äôs waaay too young to have kids.
Hey! My mom had me at sixteen.
I guess she‚Äôd have to be.
It makes sense that you‚Äôre the older sister.
Idk, you‚Äôve got that smart, sensible vibe about you.
We‚Äôve been through a fire together.
I think it has to do with my father.
Did he hate music, or something?
He played piano when I was a kid.
And we used to sing together.
But when Dad left, my mom was just angry all the time.
She smashed up the piano, and sold all the records they bought together.
We never played music at home after Dad left.
I can‚Äôt imagine a home without music.
My place, there‚Äôs someone strumming a guitar 24/7.
Being stuck in a place with no music reminds me of prison.
It‚Äôs not as bad as it sounds.
Worst six weeks of my life.
My mom was in tears every time I called home.
My brothers didn‚Äôt have anyone to look out for them.
I broke into Lincoln Park Zoo.
Let these guys out of their cages.
I kinda saw myself as a freedom fighter.
But that‚Äôs all behind me now.
Besides, I was never a bad guy, just a little wild.
Now I got my bike shop.
My little brother works for me.
I gotta look out for him.
The wildest thing I do is play in my band at weekends.
You‚Äôve never done anything against the law?
Snuck in the back door of a movie theatre?
Taken sugar or napkins from a diner?
We all break the law sometimes.
Will you go on a date with me?
We‚Äôre not going to rob a bank, are we?
While you make jokes about naked photos?
So where are you taking me?
Not some spit and sawdust blues bar?
Aren‚Äôt there experiments about that, science girl?
I heard it releases those endo things.
Well, maybe a little sad about that imaginary fire.
Listen, if you haven‚Äôt sung since you were a kid, we need to fix that.
That has never been one of my mottos.
I say, better safe than sorry.
That‚Äôs why life has thrown us together.
What kinda life you gonna live if you don‚Äôt try things that scare you?
I told you ‚Äî a safe life.
The karaoke place I like has great food.
Japanese fusion type stuff, like sushi and dumplings.
That‚Äôs what your dating profile says.
Okay. But first you have to agree to come to karaoke with me.
We can eat Japanese food, and I‚Äôll sing to you.
All you have to do is eat and listen.
See? I can be a gentleman.
But you‚Äôll be the only one singing.
When we‚Äôre at the karaoke bar.
